    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.26a.39" />
                
                <fw type="curatorial">39</fw>
                
                <fw type="letterhead">
                    <hi rend="caps">THE WENTZVILLE UNION
                        <lb/>
                    WEEKLY NEWSPAPER
                        <lb/>
                    ========================================================
                        <lb/>
                    WENTZVILLE, MISSOURI
                        <lb/>
                    TELEPHONE FAIRVIEW</hi> 7-6220
                </fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>April 21, 1958</dateline>
                
                    <salute>Dear Dr. Neihardt,</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>My wife and I join your many friends in the sorrow of your loss. Our sorrow in<sic>is</sic> tempered, however, in the knowledge that you, perhaps better than others, understand the process of life and can accept your new lonliness in a good spirit.</p>
                
                <p>Your words, ideas, books and personality are a part of our lives and will be passed on to our children. We shall always be your students and shall always love you dearly.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>Sincerely,</salute>
                    
                    <signed>Ralph Dermmit</signed>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
        
